* Tag migration::
@end menu

@node Tag migration
@section Tag migration

@findex org2blog-extras-move-tags-to-drawer
WordPress assigns tags to posts through the @samp{POST_TAGS} property in the Org heading's property drawer, but you may already have tags defined in the standard Org tag format (@samp{:tag1:tag2:} at the end of the heading line). The command @code{org2blog-extras-move-tags-to-drawer} scans the current buffer for headings with Org tags, converts them to a comma-separated string, and stores the result in the @samp{POST_TAGS} property.

For example, a heading like @samp{* My Post :emacs:org:} would gain a property @samp{POST_TAGS} with the value @samp{"emacs, org"}. The command processes all headings in the buffer from the current position forward, so you should typically invoke it with point at the beginning of the buffer.

Note that this command does not remove the original Org tags from the heading line. You may want to remove them manually after running the command if they are no longer needed.

@node Advice
@chapter Advice

@menu
* Conditional publishing confirmation::
@end menu

@node Conditional publishing confirmation
@section Conditional publishing confirmation

@findex org2blog-extras-subtree-publish-save
The @samp{org2blog} variable @code{org2blog/wp-confirm-post}, when set to @code{t}, causes every publishing operation to prompt for confirmation. This is a useful safety net for new posts, but it becomes tedious when you are iterating on an already-published post or page.

The function @code{org2blog-extras-subtree-publish-save} is installed as @samp{:around} advice on both @code{org2blog-subtree-post-save} and @code{org2blog-subtree-page-save}. It checks whether the current post or page has a @samp{post-id} property (indicating it has been published before):

@itemize
@item
If a @samp{post-id} exists, the original publishing function is called directly without any confirmation prompt. This makes rapid updates frictionless.
@item
If no @samp{post-id} exists, the advice prompts with ``Post has no ID@. Proceed anyway?'' before allowing publication. This prevents accidental creation of new posts.
@end itemize

This advice is applied automatically when @samp{org2blog-extras.el} is loaded. It replaces the blanket confirmation with a context-sensitive check that protects against unintended first publications while streamlining updates.

